Located in the mountains of Guiyang Qianling Park, Qianling Mountain Zoo is situated on the depression platform of Zhangbofeng Mountain. It is a garden for breeding and researching wildlife and exploring the mysteries of nature. The Qianlingshan Zoo, which covers an area of 7.55 hectares, was built in 1958. The terrain is relatively flat and the terrain rises from the gate to the back. Various cages and feeding grounds in Qianlingshan Zoo are built in the valley along the mountain. There are panda specimen exhibition rooms in the Langur Monkey Pavilion, Xiongchi Deer Park in the Lion Tiger Pavilion and so on. The cage covers an area of 3300 square meters. There are more than 40 animals and more than 200 head animals on display. Among them, there are rare animals, such as the white tiger, the northeastern tiger, the African lion, the leopard, the peacock, the ostrich, the great Swan and antelope, and the rare animals, such as the black langur pheasant, the red-bellied pheasant, the white pheasant and so on. Inside and outside the garden, Cui Ling is surrounded by birds and flowers. It has become an important place for tourists and youngsters to enjoy entertainment, science popularization and ecological protection.
